qas.question: The Medieval period begins with the fall of what city?
What can Plainsong or Gregorian chant also be called?
When did Monophonic chant stop being the dominant form?
Polyphonic music included more complex voicing of what?

context: The Medieval period includes music from after the fall of <a0_0>Rome<a0_0/> to about 1400. <a1_0>Monophonic chant<a1_0/>, also called plainsong or Gregorian chant, was the dominant form until about <a3_0>1100<a3_0/>. Polyphonic (<a2_0>multi-voiced<a2_0/>) music developed from monophonic chant throughout the late Middle Ages and into the Renaissance, including the more complex voicings of <a4_0>motets<a4_0/>.
